[SAY] Back in normal mode. Works just like Escape for basic editing.
[SAY] The difference is subtle. If you have abbreviations set up, Escape triggers them. Control C does not. For most editing, both work the same.
[SAY] Enter insert again.
[KEYS] 'A'
[OVERLAY] ⇧A  append

